rect.title: Distance of the mass from its equilibrium position in a particular direction. ( Equilibrium position: position where net force = 0 )
number of oscillations per unit time.
Angular frequency is defined by the equation = 2f where f is the number of oscillations per unit time.

Simple harmonic motion is an oscillatory motion (of an object) where the acceleration is 1.always proportional to, and 2.opposite in direction to the displacement from a certain fixed point / equilibrium position
Damping refers to the loss of energy from an oscillating system to the environment, due to dissipative forces, causing its amplitude to decrease with time.
System oscillates about the equilibrium position with decreasing amplitude. Amplitude {not: displacement} of the system decreases exponentially with time
Damping is so great that the displaced object never oscillates but returns to its equilibrium position very very slowly.
Damping is just sufficient for the time taken for the displacement to return to zero is a minimum. System does not oscillate (similar to case of heavy damping)
An oscillating system is said to be undergoing free oscillations if: its oscillations are not subjected to an external periodic driving force. Hence the system oscillates at its natural frequency.

An oscillating system is said to undergo forced oscillations if: subjected to an external periodic driving force. frequency of the forced (or driven) oscillations will be at the frequency of the driving force.

Resonance is a phenomenon whereby the amplitude of a system undergoing forced oscillations is at a maximum. It occurs when the frequency of the periodic driving force is equal to the natural frequency of the system.
